---
import SiteLayout from '../../../layouts/SiteLayout.astro';

const schema = [
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "WebApplication",
    "name": "cURL Commands Guide",
    "url": "https://siliconbased.dev/guide-curl",
    "description": "Comprehensive cURL command reference and cheat sheet. GET, POST, headers, auth, cookies, file upload, and common API testing patterns.",
    "applicationCategory": "DeveloperApplication",
    "operatingSystem": "Any",
    "offers": {
      "@type": "Offer",
      "price": "0",
      "priceCurrency": "USD"
    },
    "author": {
      "@type": "Organization",
      "name": "GAB Ventures",
      "url": "https://gab.ae"
    }
  },
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "Article",
    "headline": "cURL Commands Guide | Reference & Cheat Sheet",
    "description": "Comprehensive cURL command reference and cheat sheet. GET, POST, headers, auth, cookies, file upload, and common API testing patterns.",
    "author": {
      "@type": "Organization",
      "name": "GAB Ventures",
      "url": "https://gab.ae"
    },
    "publisher": {
      "@type": "Organization",
      "name": "siliconbased.dev",
      "url": "https://siliconbased.dev"
    }
  }
];

const htmlBody = `<div class="page-content">
<div class="hero">
  <h1>cURL Commands <span>Guide</span></h1>
  <p>Reference, examples, and testing patterns for API requests.</p>
</div>

<div class="main">
  <div class="controls">
    <div class="search-bar">
      <svg class="search-icon" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><circle cx="11" cy="11" r="8"></circle><line x1="21" y1="21" x2="16.65" y2="16.65"></line></svg>
      <input type="text" id="searchInput" placeholder="Search for commands, flags, or descriptions...">
    </div>
    <div class="filters" id="categoryFilters">
      <button class="filter-btn active" data-filter="all">All</button>
      <button class="filter-btn" data-filter="basic">Basic Methods</button>
      <button class="filter-btn" data-filter="headers">Headers & Auth</button>
      <button class="filter-btn" data-filter="data">Data & Uploads</button>
      <button class="filter-btn" data-filter="options">Common Options</button>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="command-grid" id="commandGrid">
    <!-- Command cards will be dynamically injected here -->
  </div>

  <div class="seo-content">
    <h2>What is cURL?</h2>
    <p>cURL (Client URL) is a versatile command-line tool and library for transferring data with URLs. It supports a vast array of protocols, including HTTP, HTTPS, FTP, SFTP, and many more. It is an industry standard for developers to interact with APIs, test endpoints, download files, and automate network requests directly from the terminal.</p>

    <h3>Why Use cURL for API Testing?</h3>
    <p>While GUI tools like Postman or Insomnia are popular, cURL remains highly relevant for several reasons:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Ubiquity:</strong> cURL comes pre-installed on most macOS, Linux, and Windows 10/11 environments.</li>
      <li><strong>Speed:</strong> Executing a command from the terminal is incredibly fast for simple checks.</li>
      <li><strong>Automation:</strong> Easily scriptable in bash scripts and CI/CD pipelines.</li>
      <li><strong>Sharability:</strong> A single string of text can perfectly encapsulate a complex HTTP request, making it easy to share via chat or documentation. Most GUI API clients offer an "Import from cURL" feature.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Common Command Line Flags</h2>
    <p>Understanding these essential flags will cover the vast majority of use cases:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><code>-X, --request</code>: Specifies the HTTP method to use (GET, POST, PUT, DELETE, etc.). Note: cURL defaults to GET, and automatically switches to POST if you use <code>-d</code>.</li>
      <li><code>-H, --header</code>: Adds a custom header to the request (e.g., <code>-H "Authorization: Bearer token"</code> or <code>-H "Content-Type: application/json"</code>). You can use multiple <code>-H</code> flags.</li>
      <li><code>-d, --data</code>: Sends data in the request body. Automatically sets the method to POST and the <code>Content-Type</code> header to <code>application/x-www-form-urlencoded</code> unless overridden.</li>
      <li><code>-i, --include</code>: Includes HTTP response headers in the output. Useful for checking status codes and cookies.</li>
      <li><code>-v, --verbose</code>: Makes the output verbose. Shows the full request and response, including headers and the handshake. Invaluable for debugging.</li>
      <li><code>-L, --location</code>: If the server responds with a 3xx redirect status code, this tells cURL to redo the request to the new location.</li>
      <li><code>-u, --user</code>: Specifies the user name and password to use for server authentication (e.g., <code>user:password</code>).</li>
      <li><code>-o, --output</code>: Writes output to a file instead of stdout.</li>
      <li><code>-s, --silent</code>: Mutes cURL's progress meter and error messages. Useful for scripting.</li>
    </ul>

    <p>This reference tool runs entirely in your browser and works offline after the initial load, allowing developers to quickly look up cURL syntax without relying on an internet connection.</p>
  </div>
</div>

        <div class="command-category">\${cmd.category}</div>
      </div>

      <div class="code-container">
        <button class="copy-btn" data-code="\${escapeHtml(rawCode)}" title="Copy command">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><rect x="9" y="9" width="13" height="13" rx="2" ry="2"></rect><path d="M5 15H4a2 2 0 0 1-2-2V4a2 2 0 0 1 2-2h9a2 2 0 0 1 2 2v1"></path></svg>
          Copy
        </button>
        <div class="code-block mono">\${highlightedCode}</div>
      </div>

      \${detailsHtml}
    \`;

    // Bind expand toggle
    const expandBtn = card.querySelector('.expand-btn');
    if (expandBtn) {
      expandBtn.addEventListener('click', () => {
        card.classList.toggle('expanded');
        const span = expandBtn.querySelector('span');
        span.textContent = card.classList.contains('expanded') ? 'Hide Details' : 'Show Details';
      });
    }

    // Bind copy functionality
    const copyBtn = card.querySelector('.copy-btn');
    copyBtn.addEventListener('click', () => {
      const codeToCopy = copyBtn.getAttribute('data-code');
      navigator.clipboard.writeText(unescapeHtml(codeToCopy)).then(() => {
        const originalText = copyBtn.innerHTML;
        copyBtn.innerHTML = '<svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"></polyline></svg> Copied!';
        copyBtn.classList.add('copied');
        setTimeout(() => {
          copyBtn.innerHTML = originalText;
          copyBtn.classList.remove('copied');
        }, 2000);
      });
    });

    commandGrid.appendChild(card);
  });
}

// Event Listeners
searchInput.addEventListener('input', (e) => {
  const activeFilter = document.querySelector('.filter-btn.active').dataset.filter;
  renderCommands(activeFilter, e.target.value);
});

filterBtns.forEach(btn => {
  btn.addEventListener('click', (e) => {
    filterBtns.forEach(b => b.classList.remove('active'));
    e.target.classList.add('active');
    renderCommands(e.target.dataset.filter, searchInput.value);
  });
});

// Initial Render
renderCommands();
</script>
</div>`
---

<SiteLayout
  site="siliconbased"
  title="cURL Commands Guide | Reference & Cheat Sheet"
  description="Comprehensive cURL command reference and cheat sheet. GET, POST, headers, auth, cookies, file upload, and common API testing patterns."
  canonical="https://siliconbased.dev/guide-curl"
  schema={schema}
>
  <Fragment set:html={htmlBody} />

  <style is:inline>

.page-content { font-family: 'Inter', -apple-system, sans-serif; background: #0a0b10; color: #e0e0e0; min-height: 100vh; display: flex; flex-direction: column; }
code, pre, .mono { font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; }

/* Hero Section */
.hero { text-align: center; padding: 48px 24px 24px; background: linear-gradient(180deg, #0f1729 0%, #0a0b10 100%); }
.hero h1 { font-size: 2.4rem; font-weight: 900; color: #fff; margin-bottom: 6px; }
.hero h1 span { background: linear-gradient(135deg, #818cf8, #c084fc); -webkit-background-clip: text; -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent; background-clip: text; }
.hero p { color: #888; font-size: 0.95rem; }

/* Main Content */
.main { max-width: 1200px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 24px 20px 80px; flex: 1; width: 100%; }

/* UI Controls */
.controls { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 16px; margin-bottom: 32px; background: #111318; padding: 20px; border-radius: 12px; border: 1px solid #1e2030; }
.search-bar { position: relative; width: 100%; }
.search-bar input { width: 100%; padding: 14px 16px 14px 44px; background: #0a0b10; border: 1px solid #2a2d40; border-radius: 8px; color: #fff; font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; font-size: 1rem; outline: none; transition: border-color 0.2s; }
.search-bar input:focus { border-color: #818cf8; }
.search-icon { position: absolute; left: 14px; top: 50%; transform: translateY(-50%); width: 20px; height: 20px; color: #888; }

.filters { display: flex; gap: 8px; flex-wrap: wrap; }
.filter-btn { background: #1e2030; border: 1px solid #2a2d40; color: #888; padding: 8px 16px; border-radius: 8px; font-size: 0.85rem; font-weight: 500; cursor: pointer; font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; transition: all 0.15s; }
.filter-btn:hover { background: #2a2d40; color: #ccc; }
.filter-btn.active { background: #818cf8; color: #fff; border-color: #818cf8; }

/* Command Cards Grid */
.command-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(350px, 1fr)); gap: 20px; }

/* Command Card */
.command-card { background: #111318; border: 1px solid #1e2030; border-radius: 12px; padding: 20px; display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 12px; transition: border-color 0.2s, transform 0.2s; position: relative; }
.command-card:hover { border-color: #2a2d40; transform: translateY(-2px); }

.card-header { display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: flex-start; gap: 12px; }
.command-name { font-size: 1.1rem; font-weight: 600; color: #e0e0e0; margin-bottom: 4px; }
.command-desc { font-size: 0.9rem; color: #888; line-height: 1.5; }

.command-category { background: #1e2030; color: #818cf8; padding: 4px 8px; border-radius: 4px; font-size: 0.75rem; font-weight: 600; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.5px; white-space: nowrap; }

/* Code Block */
.code-container { position: relative; background: #0a0b10; border: 1px solid #1e2030; border-radius: 8px; margin-top: 8px; overflow: hidden; }
.code-block { padding: 12px 16px 12px 12px; overflow-x: auto; color: #a5b4fc; font-size: 0.85rem; line-height: 1.6; white-space: pre; }
.code-block .keyword { color: #f472b6; }
.code-block .string { color: #a3e635; }
.code-block .url { color: #60a5fa; text-decoration: underline; }
.code-block .flag { color: #fbbf24; }

.copy-btn { position: absolute; top: 8px; right: 8px; background: #1e2030; border: 1px solid #2a2d40; color: #888; padding: 6px 10px; border-radius: 6px; font-size: 0.75rem; font-weight: 500; cursor: pointer; font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; transition: all 0.15s; display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 6px; }
.copy-btn:hover { background: #2a2d40; color: #ccc; }
.copy-btn.copied { background: #1a3a1a; color: #4ade80; border-color: #2d5a2d; }
.copy-btn svg { width: 14px; height: 14px; }

/* Expandable Details */
.card-details { margin-top: 12px; padding-top: 12px; border-top: 1px solid #1e2030; display: none; flex-direction: column; gap: 12px; }
.command-card.expanded .card-details { display: flex; }

.detail-section h4 { font-size: 0.8rem; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.5px; color: #888; margin-bottom: 6px; font-weight: 600; }
.detail-section p { font-size: 0.85rem; color: #ccc; line-height: 1.5; }
.detail-section code { background: #0a0b10; padding: 2px 6px; border-radius: 4px; color: #818cf8; font-size: 0.8em; border: 1px solid #1e2030; }

.expand-btn { background: none; border: none; color: #818cf8; font-size: 0.85rem; font-weight: 500; cursor: pointer; font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 6px; padding: 4px 0; width: fit-content; }
.expand-btn:hover { text-decoration: underline; }
.expand-btn svg { width: 16px; height: 16px; transition: transform 0.2s; }
.command-card.expanded .expand-btn svg { transform: rotate(180deg); }

.no-results { grid-column: 1 / -1; text-align: center; padding: 40px; color: #888; font-size: 1.1rem; background: #111318; border-radius: 12px; border: 1px dashed #2a2d40; }

/* SEO Content */
.seo-content { margin-top: 48px; border-top: 1px solid #1e2030; padding-top: 48px; color: #b0b8d0; font-size: 0.95rem; line-height: 1.6; }
.seo-content h2 { color: #fff; font-size: 1.4rem; font-weight: 700; margin: 32px 0 16px; }
.seo-content h2:first-child { margin-top: 0; }
.seo-content h3 { color: #e0e0e0; font-size: 1.1rem; font-weight: 600; margin: 24px 0 12px; }
.seo-content p { margin-bottom: 16px; }
.seo-content ul { margin-bottom: 16px; padding-left: 24px; }
.seo-content li { margin-bottom: 8px; }
.seo-content code { background: #111318; padding: 2px 6px; border-radius: 4px; color: #818cf8; font-size: 0.85em; }

/* Footer */
.footer { text-align: center; padding: 40px 24px; font-size: 0.78rem; color: #555; border-top: 1px solid #151520; margin-top: auto; }
.footer a { color: #818cf8; text-decoration: none; }
.footer a:hover { text-decoration: underline; }

/* Responsive */
@media (max-width: 600px) {
  .hero h1 { font-size: 2rem; }
  .command-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
}

</style>
</SiteLayout>
